<h2>David's Latest Posts</h2>
	
				
		
			<div class="post-17041 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-missiles-missile-defense tag-missile tag-north-korea">

				<div class="post-17041 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-missiles-missile-defense tag-missile tag-north-korea" id="post-17041">    
					<div class="latest-posts-post">

												<a href="https://allthingsnuclear.org/dwright/north-koreas-latest-missile-test" class="post_thumbnail no-image">
							<span></span>
						</a>

						<div class="post_details_inner">
							<h1>
								<a href="https://allthingsnuclear.org/dwright/north-koreas-latest-missile-test" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to North Korea&#8217;s Latest Missile Test">
								North Korea&#8217;s Latest Missile Test								</a>
							</h1>
														<div class="post-date ">
								<p>October 1, 2019 10:19 PM EDT</p>
							</div>
							<div class="article-content">                    
								<p>Various <a href="https://twitter.com/nktpnd/status/1179215094179336192">sources</a> are reporting that North Korea test-launched two ballistic missiles tonight on lofted trajectories.</p>
<p>One of the missiles is reported to have reached a maximum altitude of 910 km (570 miles) and splashed down at a range of 450 km (280 miles) from the launch point. This missile would have had a burnout speed of about 3.74 km/s with a loft angle of 81.5 degrees, and a flight time of about 17 minutes.</p>
<p>If flown on a standard trajectory with the same payload, that missile would have a maximum range of about 1,900 km (1,200 miles).</p>
<p>This would classify the missile as medium range (1,000 to 3,500 km).</p>
								  								  <div class="addthis_widget"><a class="addthis_button" addthis:url="https://allthingsnuclear.org/?p=17041" addthis:title="North Korea&#8217;s Latest Missile Test" href="https://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&amp;pubid=ra-4dd154a4387f0255"><img src="https://s7.addthis.com/static/btn/sm-share-en.gif" width="83" height="16" alt="Bookmark and Share" style="border:0"/></a></div>							</div>
						</div>

